and what about the human freedom human emancipation and the radical imagination events at stanford and what about the human freedom human emancipation and the radical imagination facebook twitter email print add to calendar anthony bogues harmon family professor of africana studes brown university this talk will explore the notion that there is a distinct difference between emancipation and freedom working through an argument that the question of the human is not just an ethical nor moral one but rather political the talk will argue that to think about freedom today is to think about the meaning of the human it will suggest that issues of freedom are deeply related to the work of the imagination when thursday february 16 2012 3 30 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where humanities center levinthal hall 424 santa teresa street map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags other humanities sponsor humanities center contact 650 725 1219 pmsumana stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 308 30801 more info last modified february 14 2012
